&lt;p&gt;Keep in mind it’s OK to do nothing at all, too.&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 26 Apr 2021 05:22:28 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Untangling Haskell's Strings</title><link>https://mmhaskell.com/blog/2017/5/15/untangling-haskells-strings</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/7gxlyn/untangling_haskell_s_strings"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 25 Apr 2021 20:39:04 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Parsing Protobuf at 2+GB/s: How I Learned To Love Tail Calls in C</title><link>https://blog.reverberate.org/2021/04/21/musttail-efficient-interpreters.html</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/ffssdz/parsing_protobuf_at_2_gb_s_how_i_learned"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 25 Apr 2021 01:05:33 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>What's in an Emacs Lambda (2017)</title><link>https://nullprogram.com/blog/2017/12/14/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/zof2kh/what_s_emacs_lambda_2017"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 25 Apr 2021 17:39:50 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>PinePhone Keyboard to make for a cheaper, albeit slower Cosmo Communicator</title><link>https://www.cnx-software.com/2021/04/26/pinephone-keyboard-to-make-for-a-cheaper-albeit-slower-cosmo-communicator/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/qb4dzi/pinephone_keyboard_make_for_cheaper"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 26 Apr 2021 06:36:35 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Red &amp; blue functions are actually a good thing</title><link>https://blainehansen.me/post/red-blue-functions-are-actually-good/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/fdmjcm/red_blue_functions_are_actually_good"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 26 Apr 2021 05:54:27 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Global Socket: Connect like there is no firewall. Securely</title><link>https://www.gsocket.io/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/fhpswy/global_socket_connect_like_there_is_no"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 25 Apr 2021 10:54:47 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Security Researcher Dan Kaminsky Passes Away</title><link>https://lobste.rs/s/jguw6i</link><description>&lt;div dir="ltr"&gt;
By &lt;a href="https://www.securityweek.com/authors/securityweek-news" dir="ltr"&gt;SecurityWeek News&lt;/a&gt; on April 24, 2021 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Celebrated Hacker Dan Kaminsky Dead at 42&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span dir="ltr"&gt;The cybersecurity world woke up Saturday to news of the sudden passing of &lt;strong dir="ltr"&gt;Dan Kaminsky (&lt;a href="https://twitter.com/dakami" dir="ltr"&gt;@dakami&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/strong&gt;, a celebrated hacker who is widely credited with pioneering research work on DNS security.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="https://www.securityweek.com/sites/default/files/logos/Dan_Kaminsky.jpg" alt="Dan Kaminsky" title="Security Researcher Dan Kaminsky Dead at 42" width="200" height="309"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Kaminsky was 42.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;A regular speaker at Black Hat and DEFCON conferences over the years, Kaminsky was most recently co-founder and chief scientist at Human Security (formerly known as White Ops), an anti-fraud startup.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;He is best known for his groundbreaking DNS cache-poisoning research that prompted an industry-wide scramble to address a major weakness in the way the web worked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Kaminsky is also credited with amplifying the severity of the SONY rootkit infections back in 2005.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;In June 2010, Kaminsky was named by ICANN as one of the Trusted Community Representatives for the DNSSEC root.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="https://www.securityweek.com/sites/all/modules/ad/serve.php?o=image&amp;amp;a=1296" height="0" width="0" alt="view counter"&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 24 Apr 2021 16:44:21 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Himalaya, the CLI email client: v0.2.7 released</title><link>https://lobste.rs/s/ifmf7z</link><description>&lt;h3&gt;Added&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;UL&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Default page size to config [&lt;a data-error-text="Failed to load title" data-id="856587995" data-permission-text="Title is private" data-url="https://github.com/soywod/himalaya/issues/96" data-hovercard-type="issue" data-hovercard-url="/soywod/himalaya/issues/96/hovercard" href="https://github.com/soywod/himalaya/issues/96" dir="ltr"&gt;#96&lt;/a&gt;]&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Custom config path [&lt;a data-error-text="Failed to load title" data-id="854757198" data-permission-text="Title is private" data-url="https://github.com/soywod/himalaya/issues/86" data-hovercard-type="issue" data-hovercard-url="/soywod/himalaya/issues/86/hovercard" href="https://github.com/soywod/himalaya/issues/86" dir="ltr"&gt;#86&lt;/a&gt;]&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Setting idle-hook-cmds&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Changed&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;UL&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Plain logger with &lt;code dir="ltr"&gt;env_logger&lt;/code&gt; [&lt;a data-error-text="Failed to load title" data-id="866764963" data-permission-text="Title is private" data-url="https://github.com/soywod/himalaya/issues/126" data-hovercard-type="issue" data-hovercard-url="/soywod/himalaya/issues/126/hovercard" href="https://github.com/soywod/himalaya/issues/126" dir="ltr"&gt;#126&lt;/a&gt;]&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Refresh email list on load buffer [&lt;a data-error-text="Failed to load title" data-id="866683160" data-permission-text="Title is private" data-url="https://github.com/soywod/himalaya/issues/125" data-hovercard-type="issue" data-hovercard-url="/soywod/himalaya/issues/125/hovercard" href="https://github.com/soywod/himalaya/issues/125" dir="ltr"&gt;#125&lt;/a&gt;]&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Fixed&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;UL&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Improve config compatibility on Windows &lt;a href="https://github.com/soywod/himalaya/pull/111" data-hovercard-type="pull_request" data-hovercard-url="/soywod/himalaya/pull/111/hovercard" dir="ltr"&gt;#111&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Vim table containing emoji [&lt;a data-error-text="Failed to load title" data-id="865881301" data-permission-text="Title is private" data-url="https://github.com/soywod/himalaya/issues/122" data-hovercard-type="issue" data-hovercard-url="/soywod/himalaya/issues/122/hovercard" href="https://github.com/soywod/himalaya/issues/122" dir="ltr"&gt;#122&lt;/a&gt;]&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span&gt;Assets&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span title="5"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 24 Apr 2021 16:57:57 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>String interning in Go (2018)</title><link>https://artem.krylysov.com/blog/2018/12/12/string-interning-in-go/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/3bnvey/string_interning_go_2018"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 25 Apr 2021 18:23:55 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>NetBSD VM on bhyve (on TrueNAS)</title><link>https://bentsukun.ch/posts/bhyve-netbsd/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/46opnh/netbsd_vm_on_bhyve_on_truenas"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 25 Apr 2021 17:21:43 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Wayland Explorer</title><link>https://lobste.rs/s/0xkm30</link><description>&lt;h2&gt;Wayland Explorer&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;A better way to read Wayland documentation&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The most popular Wayland protocols all in one place and without having to sift through different repositories and XML files.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;Start by reading the &lt;a href="https://wayland.app/protocols/wayland" dir="ltr"&gt;core Wayland protocol&lt;/a&gt; or discover some &lt;a href="https://wayland.app/protocols/xdg-decoration-unstable-v1" title="XDG decoration" dir="ltr"&gt;uncut gems&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 24 Apr 2021 14:41:06 -0500</pubDate></item></channel></rss>